                                                        <div class="gdlr-core-blog-content">Best approximation in normed linear space is a well studied subject and it has numerous applications in many other streams in analysis. The theory has some nice interplay with the geometry of the unit ball and the differentiability of the dual norm. If the best approximation is guaranteed for a given subspace, it is natural to study how this set of best approximation is located. Various strengthenings of best approximation comes in this context. Part I will be devoted towards some basic concepts and known results in this direction and Part II will discuss some of the speaker's recent observations.
