                                                                </div>
                                                            </div>
                                                        </div>
                                                        <div class="gdlr-core-blog-content">Reproducing Kernel Hilbert Spaces (RKHS) are function spaces. They play a major role in many applicational settings - for instance, in Kernel Methods in Machine Learning, Sampling theory and Extremal problems. In this talk, after presenting the definition of an RKHS, we will see some simple examples of RKHS. Following this, we will deal with one non-trivial example of an RKHS and try to give some ideas of the proof.
